# Terminology

Use the following terms consistently. The left column is the required form. Do not use the variants
listed on the right unless they appear in code, URLs, or direct quotations from a specification.

| Required term                          | Do not use                                              |
|----------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------|
| Besu                                   | besu, BESU (except in code/URLs/CLI)                    |
| Hyperledger Besu                       | Hyperledger besu                                        |
| dapp                                   | DApp, Dapp, dApp, decentralized application             |
| externally owned account (EOA)         | externally-owned account                                |
| smart contract                         | smartcontract, smart-contract                           |
| proof of stake                         | Proof of Stake, PoS (spell out on first use)            |
| proof of work                          | Proof of Work, PoW (spell out on first use)             |
| proof of authority                     | Proof of Authority, PoA (spell out on first use)        |
| web3                                   | Web3, WEB3 (capitalize only at sentence start)          |
| JSON-RPC                               | json-rpc, Json-RPC, JSONRPC                             |
| onchain / offchain                     | on-chain, off-chain                                     |
| node                                   | full node (unless distinguishing from archive/light)    |
| consensus client                       | consensus layer client, CL client                       |
| execution client                       | execution layer client, EL client                       |
| validator                              | validator node (use "validator" in prose)                |

## Consensus protocols (private networks)

| Required term | Do not use                     |
|---------------|--------------------------------|
| IBFT 2.0      | IBFT2, ibft2, iBFT             |
| QBFT          | qbft, Qbft                     |

## Standards and specifications

When introducing a standard for the first time on a page, spell out the full name with the
identifier in parentheses. Use the short form on subsequent references.

Examples:

- First use: "Ethereum Improvement Proposal 1559 (EIP-1559)"
- Subsequent: "EIP-1559"
- First use: "Engine API specification"
- Subsequent: "Engine API"
